-- 2010-10-05T07:44:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/enbw-to-sell-36-stake-in-evn-for-675-million-in-joint-capital-increase.html
EnBW Energie Baden-Wuerttemberg AG
will sell its 36 percent stake in EVN AG for about 491 million
euros ($675 million) in a joint capital increase with the
Austrian utility.  EVN will raise about 196 million euros selling up to
16,352,582 new shares with a price range of 10.5 euros to 13.5
euros, according to a statement from EVN today.  The subscription ratio will be 10 to 1, EVN said. The over
period for the new shares and the EnBWâ€™s stake is expected to
start on Oct. 6 and end on Oct. 20. This is a public offering to
Austrian investors and a prive placement to international
investros, according to EVN.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
